WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:00:34.350 --> 00:00:37.649
<i>Welcome back. folks.</i>
<i>This is Gotham Talk Radio.</i>

3
00:00:37.821 --> 00:00:41.757
<i>Give us a call at 555-7630.</i>

4
00:00:41.925 --> 00:00:46.419
<i>Tonight. I promise. we're not going to</i>
<i>talk about President Luthor's impeachment.</i>

5
00:00:46.596 --> 00:00:48.496
<i>Instead. I wanna switch gears...</i>

6
00:00:48.665 --> 00:00:51.862
<i>...to Gotham's new fleet</i>
<i>of automated surveillance blimps...</i>

7
00:00:52.035 --> 00:00:54.162
<i>...which took flight earlier this week.</i>

8
00:00:54.337 --> 00:00:59.240
<i>Are these unmanned eyes in the sky</i>
<i>a black eye on people's privacy?</i>

9
00:01:01.244 --> 00:01:04.111
<i>That's what civil liberty groups</i>
<i>are saying. What about you?</i>

10
00:01:04.280 --> 00:01:08.239
<i>Before we get to your calls.</i>
<i>here's headline news. Vicki?</i>

11
00:01:08.752 --> 00:01:12.381
<i>A.J.. blimps aren't the only sights</i>
<i>we've been seeing these last few nights.</i>

12
00:01:12.555 --> 00:01:16.252
<i>A rash of meteor showers has lit up</i>
<i>the skies from coast to coast this week...</i>

13
00:01:16.426 --> 00:01:21.363
<i>...following the destruction of a giant</i>
<i>kryptonite asteroid by our own dark knight.</i>

14
00:01:21.531 --> 00:01:24.466
<i>Today. NASA officials. who have been</i>
<i>monitoring the situation...</i>

15
00:01:24.634 --> 00:01:27.068
<i>...say we've seen the last</i>
<i>of these shooting stars...</i>

16
00:01:27.237 --> 00:01:31.401
<i>...since most of the kryptonite debris</i>
<i>has moved beyond Earth's orbit.</i>

17
00:01:31.875 --> 00:01:34.435
<i>Meanwhile. there's been no comment</i>
<i>from Batman...</i>

18
00:01:34.611 --> 00:01:37.842
<i>...who seems to have gone back</i>
<i>into seclusion.</i>

19
00:01:38.014 --> 00:01:39.845
<i>This morning in the nation's capital...</i>

20
00:01:40.016 --> 00:01:43.110
<i>...Superman completed his deposition</i>
<i>for the impeachment hearings.</i>

21
00:01:43.286 --> 00:01:45.379
<i>He hoped the removal</i>
<i>of President Luthor...</i>

22
00:01:45.555 --> 00:01:49.582
<i>...would usher in a new era</i>
<i>of peace and tranquillity.</i>

23
00:02:04.474 --> 00:02:07.500
<i>From what we gather. something</i>
<i>has come down near Gotham harbour.</i>

24
00:02:07.677 --> 00:02:09.235
<i>Let's take some more callers.</i>

25
00:02:09.646 --> 00:02:10.840
<i>It was unbelievable.</i>

26
00:02:11.014 --> 00:02:13.414
<i>It lit up my bedroom</i>
<i>like the middle of the day.</i>

27
00:02:13.817 --> 00:02:15.148
<i>There was this big boom...</i>

28
00:02:15.318 --> 00:02:17.377
<i>...and then the whole apartment</i>
<i>just started shaking.</i>

29
00:02:17.554 --> 00:02:19.385
<i>I was so scared.</i>

30
00:02:19.823 --> 00:02:22.849
<i>Huge fireball.</i>
<i>My neighbour said it fell in the bay.</i>

31
00:02:23.026 --> 00:02:24.357
<i>Had to be a meteor. right?</i>

32
00:02:24.527 --> 00:02:27.155
<i>I mean. what else could it have been?</i>

33
00:07:01.671 --> 00:07:04.435
Hey. check it out.

34
00:07:09.579 --> 00:07:13.709
Well. hello. beautiful.
You getting a little fresh air?

35
00:07:16.219 --> 00:07:18.949
Whoa. whoa. Slow down. honey.
What is that. Swedish?

36
00:07:19.122 --> 00:07:21.590
Hey. Gus. I think she likes you.

37
00:07:21.757 --> 00:07:26.057
Come on. sweetheart. Let old Gus give you
a private lesson in foreign relations.

38
00:07:31.234 --> 00:07:34.294
Hey. lady. Gus may be a jerk.
but you shouldn't have...

39
00:07:38.207 --> 00:07:41.199
Lady. I didn't have nothing
to do with them. Here. take it.

40
00:07:41.377 --> 00:07:43.868
It's all I got. I swear.

41
00:07:53.556 --> 00:07:54.921
Hey. man. you okay?

42
00:08:00.263 --> 00:08:02.322
Tell me what happened.

43
00:08:17.146 --> 00:08:18.443
Lady. are you all right?

44
00:08:58.955 --> 00:09:00.718
Bring her down.

45
00:09:30.186 --> 00:09:31.881
Enough.

46
00:10:41.324 --> 00:10:45.260
I don't know who you are.
but you've had enough fun for one night.

47
00:11:34.477 --> 00:11:36.672
Her DNA is definitely not human.

48
00:11:39.181 --> 00:11:40.705
Enhance.

49
00:11:40.883 --> 00:11:44.319
Extremely high concentrations
of neural stem cells.

50
00:12:21.357 --> 00:12:23.985
Her name is Kara Zor-El. from Krypton.

51
00:12:24.693 --> 00:12:25.921
She's my cousin.

52
00:12:26.095 --> 00:12:29.428
Your cousin just torched $50.000
worth of custom hardware.

53
00:12:29.865 --> 00:12:33.392
- Send me the bill.
- On a reporter's salary. right.

54
00:12:42.578 --> 00:12:45.570
"This vessel contains
my daughter. Kara Zor-El...

55
00:12:45.748 --> 00:12:47.511
...from the now dead planet Krypton.

56
00:12:48.050 --> 00:12:50.177
Treat her as you would your own child.

57
00:12:50.686 --> 00:12:52.984
She will prove a treasure for your world."

58
00:12:53.155 --> 00:12:55.521
Treasure. You're sure of the translation?

59
00:12:56.125 --> 00:12:59.959
It says treasure. Not terror. not trouble.

60
00:13:00.129 --> 00:13:02.723
Always the cynic.
You can't help yourself. can you?

61
00:13:02.898 --> 00:13:04.525
You know those tests I was running?

62
00:13:04.700 --> 00:13:07.362
Her cellular structure
is a shade more dense than yours.

63
00:13:07.536 --> 00:13:09.800
She metabolizes sunlight
more efficiently.

64
00:13:09.972 --> 00:13:12.532
It could be her youth.
It could be something else.

65
00:13:12.708 --> 00:13:15.040
Bottom line.
she might be more powerful than you.

66
00:13:15.211 --> 00:13:17.907
It makes me wonder.
So does her sudden appearance.

67
00:13:18.080 --> 00:13:19.945
I find it just a little too...

68
00:13:29.425 --> 00:13:31.825
- Speak English.
- It's attacking.

69
00:13:31.994 --> 00:13:33.018
What's attacking?

70
00:13:33.195 --> 00:13:34.662
That.

71
00:13:37.600 --> 00:13:38.794
Krypto. No.

72
00:13:40.302 --> 00:13:41.496
Bad dog.

73
00:13:41.670 --> 00:13:44.503
Kara's a friend. Leave her alone.

74
00:13:44.673 --> 00:13:46.140
I'm sorry. l...

75
00:13:46.308 --> 00:13:50.244
I've tried to get him to like me.
but he just barks and growls. he hates me.

76
00:13:50.412 --> 00:13:52.073
Go up to your quarters.

77
00:13:52.248 --> 00:13:54.648
But I didn't do anything wrong.

78
00:13:54.817 --> 00:13:56.785
We'll talk later.

79
00:14:01.924 --> 00:14:05.621
Krypto's just feeling a little overprotective.
Aren't you. boy?

80
00:14:05.794 --> 00:14:09.093
I don't know. I've always considered him
a good judge of character.

81
00:14:09.265 --> 00:14:11.062
Look. she's been through a lot.

82
00:14:11.233 --> 00:14:14.134
Not to mention learning
an entire language in less than a week.

83
00:14:14.303 --> 00:14:17.500
- Why don't you cut her some slack?
- We don't know anything about her.

84
00:14:17.673 --> 00:14:21.336
She claims to have no memory of anything
prior to splashing down in Gotham Bay.

85
00:14:21.510 --> 00:14:23.501
I'm not saying there aren't loose ends.

86
00:14:23.679 --> 00:14:26.876
Having no control over her powers
is more than a loose end.

87
00:14:27.049 --> 00:14:28.107
She's dangerous.

88
00:14:28.284 --> 00:14:32.516
Which is why she's in quarantine
until she can gain control.

89
00:14:33.022 --> 00:14:36.116
She may be the only blood relative
I have left.

90
00:14:36.292 --> 00:14:40.160
I'm willing to give her the benefit
of the doubt. at least for the time being.

91
00:14:40.329 --> 00:14:42.456
You don't have a problem with that.
do you?

92
00:14:42.631 --> 00:14:44.292
No problem at all.

93
00:14:44.466 --> 00:14:46.093
But I can't speak for the dog.

94
00:15:21.403 --> 00:15:23.371
Spying on me now?

95
00:15:23.539 --> 00:15:24.767
You don't like me. do you?

96
00:15:25.207 --> 00:15:26.834
Huh. It's you that has the problem.

97
00:15:27.009 --> 00:15:30.604
Why can't you leave me alone? You'll
never understand what it's like to be me.

98
00:15:30.779 --> 00:15:32.770
Then explain it to me until I do.

99
00:15:38.487 --> 00:15:40.921
Does any of this help
fill in your memory lapses?

100
00:15:41.090 --> 00:15:44.548
Some. I know that's my Uncle Jor-El
and my Aunt Lara.

101
00:15:44.994 --> 00:15:48.191
Because Superman. Kal-El. told you.

102
00:15:48.364 --> 00:15:50.958
No. Because I remember.

103
00:15:51.133 --> 00:15:54.068
Uncle Jor-El was like my father.

104
00:15:54.236 --> 00:15:56.830
<i>They both believed</i>
<i>the planet was doomed...</i>

105
00:15:57.006 --> 00:15:59.065
<i>...which is why my father</i>
<i>also built a ship.</i>

106
00:16:02.211 --> 00:16:05.146
<i>He told me the navigation system</i>
<i>was locked onto Earth...</i>

107
00:16:05.314 --> 00:16:08.306
<i>...and that he and my mother</i>
<i>would soon follow.</i>

108
00:16:13.689 --> 00:16:15.281
<i>I was just about out when...</i>

109
00:16:16.725 --> 00:16:20.491
<i>I saw them die. right before my eyes.</i>

110
00:16:21.330 --> 00:16:25.391
<i>And then there was that light.</i>
<i>that awful. blistering light.</i>

111
00:16:34.476 --> 00:16:38.207
Then. all I remember is darkness.

112
00:16:38.380 --> 00:16:39.904
The rest you told me.

113
00:16:40.082 --> 00:16:42.277
How the asteroid carried me
across the galaxy...

114
00:16:42.451 --> 00:16:44.316
...until it broke and I landed here.

115
00:16:44.720 --> 00:16:46.483
Do you remember your mother's name?

116
00:16:46.655 --> 00:16:48.384
You know I don't.

117
00:16:48.557 --> 00:16:49.751
Why don't you trust me?

118
00:16:50.192 --> 00:16:54.925
Kal-El has enemies who would go
to great lengths to destroy him.

119
00:16:55.097 --> 00:16:57.156
You think I would hurt my own cousin?

120
00:16:57.332 --> 00:16:58.993
Perhaps not intentionally.

121
00:17:05.074 --> 00:17:08.669
I sensed your presence earlier
because I thought I heard your heartbeat.

122
00:17:09.078 --> 00:17:10.670
I was wrong.

123
00:17:10.846 --> 00:17:12.939
You have no heart.

124
00:17:41.110 --> 00:17:46.878
My Treasure. you are one
of the finest warriors on Apocalypse.

125
00:17:47.049 --> 00:17:52.043
But do you really think you have what
it takes to be captain of the honour guard...

126
00:17:52.221 --> 00:17:55.748
...to the almighty Darkseid?

127
00:17:55.924 --> 00:17:59.325
Bring them forth
so they can taste my blade.

128
00:18:01.196 --> 00:18:02.322
Furies.

129
00:19:20.609 --> 00:19:22.509
This one was no match for us.

130
00:19:22.678 --> 00:19:24.509
Let the dogs clean up the mess.

131
00:19:26.582 --> 00:19:28.675
You disappoint me. Granny Goodness.

132
00:19:28.851 --> 00:19:33.788
You led me to believe Treasure could
replace Big Barda as captain of my guard.

133
00:19:33.956 --> 00:19:36.891
She showed such promise.

134
00:19:37.059 --> 00:19:39.527
There has been
an interesting development on Earth.

135
00:19:39.895 --> 00:19:42.022
Bring me the girl
who fell out of the sky.

136
00:19:42.197 --> 00:19:43.687
The one they call Kara.

137
00:19:44.099 --> 00:19:46.966
And this time don't fail me.

138
00:19:47.536 --> 00:19:53.304
Or it will be you. dear Granny.
whom the Furies carve up next.

139
00:20:51.133 --> 00:20:53.601
I'm so glad to be out of quarantine.
I can't tell you.

140
00:20:54.036 --> 00:20:56.436
Don't get me wrong.
I like the Fortress of Solitude.

141
00:20:56.605 --> 00:20:59.438
But you have to admit.
it is a little boring.

142
00:21:02.711 --> 00:21:04.838
Metropolis is much more my style.

143
00:21:05.814 --> 00:21:08.112
This is the life I want. Kal. Uh...

144
00:21:08.283 --> 00:21:09.875
I mean. Clark.

145
00:21:10.485 --> 00:21:12.544
You've got plenty of time to decide.

146
00:21:12.721 --> 00:21:15.781
I wanna know everything there is to know
about being an Earth girl.

147
00:21:15.958 --> 00:21:17.619
Where do we start?

148
00:21:20.262 --> 00:21:23.322
I have a pretty good idea. Come on.

149
00:21:56.231 --> 00:21:57.721
Whoa!

150
00:22:23.992 --> 00:22:25.357
Ready?

151
00:22:25.527 --> 00:22:26.858
Ta-da!

152
00:22:31.700 --> 00:22:33.167
Well?

153
00:22:33.335 --> 00:22:34.859
Uh. no way.

154
00:22:35.237 --> 00:22:37.262
Perfect. I'll take it.

155
00:22:41.276 --> 00:22:43.403
Oops. Heh-heh-heh.

156
00:22:46.915 --> 00:22:48.746
Oh. my gosh. That was so much fun.

157
00:22:48.917 --> 00:22:50.578
I'm going to love being an Earth girl.

158
00:22:50.752 --> 00:22:53.277
You've certainly got
the shopping part down.

159
00:22:53.455 --> 00:22:56.049
Are you hungry? I'm starving.

160
00:23:07.002 --> 00:23:09.664
- They're not really made out of...?
- No.

161
00:23:13.809 --> 00:23:16.437
That's so good.

162
00:23:17.846 --> 00:23:19.143
Well. that's it.

163
00:23:19.314 --> 00:23:21.214
Shopping. junk food...

164
00:23:21.383 --> 00:23:23.749
I'd say you're a bona-fide Earth girl.

165
00:23:29.224 --> 00:23:31.192
It's so beautiful here.

166
00:23:31.359 --> 00:23:33.725
Not like that other city
where Grumpy Ass lives.

167
00:23:34.362 --> 00:23:37.195
Grumpy Ass isn't so bad
once you get to know him.

168
00:23:37.365 --> 00:23:38.662
What's his problem anyway?

169
00:23:38.834 --> 00:23:41.598
He just wants you
to take things a little slower.

170
00:23:41.770 --> 00:23:45.069
Adapting to a new culture.
any culture. can be difficult.

171
00:23:45.240 --> 00:23:49.301
Is that why you wear those eyeglasses.
as a way of adapting...

172
00:23:49.478 --> 00:23:51.776
...even though you can see better
than anyone?

173
00:23:51.947 --> 00:23:57.613
It's a way for those of us who are heroes
to have lives without the cape.

174
00:23:57.786 --> 00:24:00.550
It's important to keep
our identities a secret.

175
00:24:01.089 --> 00:24:03.887
That's why Mr. Friendly never takes off
his lead-lined cowl.

176
00:24:04.359 --> 00:24:07.590
You noticed the lead. I didn't know
your x-ray vision had kicked in.

177
00:24:07.762 --> 00:24:09.593
You didn't ask.

178
00:24:10.599 --> 00:24:11.725
Oh. my.

179
00:24:17.205 --> 00:24:18.900
This is how they see you.

180
00:24:19.074 --> 00:24:20.234
Bigger than life.

181
00:24:20.742 --> 00:24:22.107
You're their champion.

182
00:24:23.945 --> 00:24:25.606
These powers.

183
00:24:25.780 --> 00:24:28.578
- Do you ever regret having them?
- No.

184
00:24:29.117 --> 00:24:31.051
Not even a little?

185
00:24:32.354 --> 00:24:33.514
Can I tell you something?

186
00:24:33.688 --> 00:24:35.485
You can tell me anything.

187
00:24:36.458 --> 00:24:37.789
They terrify me.

188
00:24:37.959 --> 00:24:41.326
I mean. the responsibility.
I don't wanna be anybody's champion.

189
00:24:42.464 --> 00:24:45.297
- No offence.
- None taken.

190
00:24:47.135 --> 00:24:49.763
- What is it?
- Stay close.

191
00:24:55.610 --> 00:24:57.475
- Guess it was... Uh!
- Kal.

192
00:25:10.825 --> 00:25:12.816
Help me. Someone. anyone.

193
00:25:13.395 --> 00:25:14.453
Kara.

194
00:25:19.768 --> 00:25:23.670
We were told you would try
to stop us. but we're taking the girl.

195
00:25:23.838 --> 00:25:26.272
She's not going anywhere.

196
00:25:41.890 --> 00:25:43.585
It may not seem like it now...

197
00:25:43.758 --> 00:25:45.055
...but this is for your own good.

198
00:25:50.031 --> 00:25:51.726
You.

199
00:25:53.401 --> 00:25:56.165
I'm sorry. but it has to be this way.

200
00:25:56.638 --> 00:25:57.969
She's right.

201
00:26:01.776 --> 00:26:03.744
I don't understand.

202
00:26:04.112 --> 00:26:06.740
Look around.
What if this had been the middle of the day?

203
00:26:06.915 --> 00:26:09.247
The park crowded with people. children.

204
00:26:09.417 --> 00:26:11.248
She needs more specialized training.

205
00:26:11.820 --> 00:26:13.082
I'm taking her with me.

206
00:26:13.488 --> 00:26:14.682
And what if I say no?

207
00:26:17.692 --> 00:26:21.184
There's another reason she can't stay.
I'll explain later.

208
00:26:21.730 --> 00:26:23.823
For now. I'm asking you to trust me.

209
00:26:24.766 --> 00:26:28.065
Kal. you're not gonna let her
take me away. are you?

210
00:26:28.236 --> 00:26:31.000
I'll work at controlling my powers.
I promise.

211
00:26:31.172 --> 00:26:32.833
Kal.

212
00:26:33.842 --> 00:26:35.503
Kal.

213
00:27:41.643 --> 00:27:43.270
Lyla. hurry.

214
00:27:43.445 --> 00:27:46.005
Kara is going up against Artemis.

215
00:27:46.181 --> 00:27:47.808
Be right there.

216
00:28:17.779 --> 00:28:19.474
Ready when you are. Artemis.

217
00:28:23.218 --> 00:28:24.776
Ready.

218
00:28:28.423 --> 00:28:29.947
Go.

219
00:28:38.600 --> 00:28:40.090
What's the point of this?

220
00:28:40.268 --> 00:28:42.065
Kara could level the entire island.

221
00:28:42.470 --> 00:28:45.769
Having power and knowing how to use it
aren't the same thing.

222
00:28:45.940 --> 00:28:48.170
You of all people should know that.

223
00:28:49.411 --> 00:28:51.436
She's getting on my nerves.

224
00:28:51.613 --> 00:28:52.875
I heard that too.

225
00:29:13.568 --> 00:29:16.230
Now. little one. prepare... Uh!

226
00:29:17.305 --> 00:29:19.205
Don't touch her.

227
00:29:19.374 --> 00:29:22.537
Kal. it's a training exercise.
She wasn't going to hurt me.

228
00:29:23.111 --> 00:29:24.203
Is there a problem?

229
00:29:24.379 --> 00:29:27.678
You asked me to keep an open mind?
Well. I've kept an open mind.

230
00:29:27.849 --> 00:29:30.545
But Kara belongs in Metropolis with me.

231
00:29:30.952 --> 00:29:32.943
We agreed this was in her best interest.

232
00:29:33.488 --> 00:29:35.319
Wait a minute. don't I have a say?

233
00:29:35.490 --> 00:29:36.957
- No.
- No.

234
00:29:38.493 --> 00:29:40.518
I'm sorry. of course you do.

235
00:29:40.695 --> 00:29:43.755
But you've been hidden away
on Paradise Island for two months now.

236
00:29:44.399 --> 00:29:46.993
You don't know
what the rest of the world has to offer.

237
00:29:47.168 --> 00:29:49.534
Who else is suited to decide
what's right for you?

238
00:29:49.904 --> 00:29:51.098
How about me?

239
00:29:51.272 --> 00:29:52.762
You let them bring me here...

240
00:29:52.941 --> 00:29:56.138
...and now because you have a problem
with it. you want me to return?

241
00:29:56.311 --> 00:29:58.871
I'm tired of being jerked around.
treated like a child.

242
00:29:59.481 --> 00:30:02.882
From now on.
I'll decide what's best for me.

243
00:30:05.520 --> 00:30:07.044
Come on. Lyla.

244
00:30:07.222 --> 00:30:10.623
Let's go before someone tries
sending me to bed without dinner.

245
00:30:16.264 --> 00:30:17.959
Don't ever do that again.

246
00:30:21.302 --> 00:30:23.736
You looked like you were ready
to snap Artemis' neck.

247
00:30:24.105 --> 00:30:26.266
Harbinger's visions show Kara in danger.

248
00:30:26.441 --> 00:30:29.069
How do you expect me to react
with a sword to her throat?

249
00:30:29.244 --> 00:30:30.802
I expect you to be rational.

250
00:30:30.979 --> 00:30:32.173
- Bruce.
- No.

251
00:30:32.347 --> 00:30:35.646
Ever since this girl came into our lives.
you've let your guard down.

252
00:30:35.817 --> 00:30:38.786
Even exposed your secret identity
despite common sense.

253
00:30:38.953 --> 00:30:42.081
Unlike you. Bruce.
I don't look for the bad in everyone.

254
00:30:42.257 --> 00:30:43.690
You may think I'm naive...

255
00:30:43.858 --> 00:30:46.986
...but my every instinct tells me
this girl is my cousin.

256
00:30:47.161 --> 00:30:50.688
She's done nothing to show me otherwise
and she'll be safe with me.

257
00:30:50.865 --> 00:30:53.356
Clark. the visions are getting worse.

258
00:30:57.739 --> 00:31:01.300
I know Kal is only trying
to protect me. but he's making me crazy.

259
00:31:01.476 --> 00:31:04.138
And everyone pretending to know
what's best for me. Agh!

260
00:31:04.812 --> 00:31:07.576
I thought I knew what I wanted.
but now...

261
00:31:07.749 --> 00:31:09.148
...I feel more lost than ever.

262
00:31:09.317 --> 00:31:13.310
Kara. when I first came here.
I was confused too.

263
00:31:13.922 --> 00:31:16.584
Able to see into the past. the future...

264
00:31:16.758 --> 00:31:20.387
...yet not having a clue
what to do with my own life.

265
00:31:20.595 --> 00:31:24.156
A harbinger for everyone but myself.

266
00:31:24.332 --> 00:31:26.493
Diana took me in without hesitation.

267
00:31:27.035 --> 00:31:29.799
If you need someone to turn to.
you can trust her.

268
00:31:29.971 --> 00:31:32.405
You've all made me feel so welcome.

269
00:31:32.574 --> 00:31:34.269
Especially you. Lyla.

270
00:31:34.442 --> 00:31:36.842
I feel like you're the only friend
I have right now.

271
00:31:44.886 --> 00:31:47.411
- Kara.
- What is it?

272
00:31:49.624 --> 00:31:52.422
Nothing. I'm just glad we're friends.

273
00:31:54.395 --> 00:31:55.987
Hey. how about a swim?

274
00:31:56.164 --> 00:31:58.189
I could use a little cooling off.

275
00:31:58.366 --> 00:32:01.358
Maybe we should get back.
Kal will be worried about you.

276
00:32:01.536 --> 00:32:03.595
Come on. one little swim.

277
00:32:03.771 --> 00:32:06.740
You're not afraid of the water. are you?

278
00:32:12.714 --> 00:32:15.615
Are you telling me
these visions are about to become a reality?

279
00:32:15.783 --> 00:32:18.843
- Lyla believes so.
- But she hasn't given us a lot to go on.

280
00:32:19.020 --> 00:32:22.046
Which is why it's just as well
we keep Kara in the dark.

281
00:32:22.223 --> 00:32:23.588
So we just keep waiting?

282
00:32:23.992 --> 00:32:27.587
This is the safest place for her. Clark.
I've had my army standing by.

283
00:32:27.762 --> 00:32:29.093
I can call them up anytime.

284
00:32:30.465 --> 00:32:31.932
Now might be good.

285
00:32:45.613 --> 00:32:46.807
Doomsday.

286
00:32:49.317 --> 00:32:51.182
Protect Kara. I'll handle this.

287
00:32:51.352 --> 00:32:53.115
Wait. the tube.

288
00:32:53.554 --> 00:32:55.613
It isn't closing.

289
00:32:58.059 --> 00:33:01.119
Darkseid. He's replicated the monster.

290
00:33:01.295 --> 00:33:05.061
Then we draw a line in the sand
and hold them here.

291
00:33:17.111 --> 00:33:18.840
Batman.

292
00:33:31.292 --> 00:33:34.659
Well?
Did you come here to sightsee or fight?

293
00:33:39.701 --> 00:33:41.191
Amazons. attack.

294
00:34:10.998 --> 00:34:12.590
There's no blood.

295
00:34:56.077 --> 00:34:57.510
Something's not right.

296
00:35:02.683 --> 00:35:04.412
Wait a minute.

297
00:35:43.324 --> 00:35:45.952
Diana. pull your army back.

298
00:35:46.460 --> 00:35:47.620
- What?
- Do it.

299
00:35:48.596 --> 00:35:50.894
Amazons. fall back.

300
00:36:02.243 --> 00:36:04.143
This ends now.

301
00:36:26.067 --> 00:36:27.295
I had no choice.

302
00:36:27.735 --> 00:36:31.136
They weren't truly alive.
No blood. no minds.

303
00:36:31.305 --> 00:36:33.136
You did what you had to do.

304
00:36:37.078 --> 00:36:38.978
Where's Batman?

305
00:36:46.354 --> 00:36:48.515
The Doomsday attack was a diversion.

306
00:36:48.689 --> 00:36:52.455
A second tube opened here.
There were four. maybe five.

307
00:36:52.627 --> 00:36:54.254
She didn't go down without a fight.

308
00:36:54.428 --> 00:36:56.157
Kara.

309
00:37:07.708 --> 00:37:09.369
Lyla.

310
00:37:42.109 --> 00:37:44.771
She died trying to protect Kara.

311
00:37:44.946 --> 00:37:48.143
I swear that her death will be avenged.

312
00:37:48.816 --> 00:37:50.283
I'm going to Apocalypse.

313
00:37:50.718 --> 00:37:52.845
That's exactly what Darkseid wants.

314
00:37:53.020 --> 00:37:54.715
Then I won't disappoint him.

315
00:37:54.889 --> 00:37:56.550
You mean we won't disappoint him.

316
00:38:02.263 --> 00:38:04.754
Let me go. you witch. Let me...

317
00:38:06.100 --> 00:38:07.124
Shut up.

318
00:38:07.301 --> 00:38:08.461
See?

319
00:38:08.636 --> 00:38:11.696
Granny has your room all ready.

320
00:38:12.073 --> 00:38:15.975
Don't worry. baby girl.
you won't be alone for long.

321
00:38:16.143 --> 00:38:18.611
Enjoy the accommodations.

322
00:38:30.958 --> 00:38:32.789
You may feel powerless now...

323
00:38:32.960 --> 00:38:35.724
...but soon you will watch the fear
in men's eyes.

324
00:38:35.896 --> 00:38:39.491
As captain of my Furies your fame
will spread throughout the universe.

325
00:38:39.667 --> 00:38:42.465
You will see the fiercest warriors
flee your presence.

326
00:38:42.636 --> 00:38:44.331
Armies brought to their knees.

327
00:38:44.505 --> 00:38:47.633
Entire nations crumble
at the mere mention of your name.

328
00:38:47.808 --> 00:38:50.299
You will know power
you would've never known on Earth.

329
00:38:50.478 --> 00:38:52.537
Never again will you be lost.

330
00:38:52.713 --> 00:38:55.079
From now on you will be at my side.

331
00:38:55.516 --> 00:38:59.577
Forever mine. forever Darkseid's.

332
00:39:23.110 --> 00:39:26.409
Over here. come on. Over here. I'm open.

333
00:39:53.908 --> 00:39:57.366
When I said drop in anytime.
this isn't quite what I pictured.

334
00:39:57.979 --> 00:39:59.037
Hello. Barda.

335
00:39:59.447 --> 00:40:03.816
Diana. You didn't leave. like.
an invisible plane in the driveway. right?

336
00:40:04.185 --> 00:40:05.709
We need to talk.

337
00:40:06.087 --> 00:40:08.385
Can I get dressed first?

338
00:40:13.561 --> 00:40:15.654
You were captain of Darkseid's honour guard.

339
00:40:16.297 --> 00:40:17.889
I defected.

340
00:40:19.900 --> 00:40:21.731
Was it easy? No.

341
00:40:22.370 --> 00:40:25.305
But for the first time. I'm free.

342
00:40:25.473 --> 00:40:27.134
And this...

343
00:40:34.248 --> 00:40:37.342
This nice. quiet. boring little life...

344
00:40:38.119 --> 00:40:39.416
...it's all mine.

345
00:40:39.820 --> 00:40:41.082
We need your help. Barda.

346
00:40:41.255 --> 00:40:43.587
Darkseid has kidnapped my cousin. Kara.

347
00:40:44.191 --> 00:40:46.022
Then she is lost to you.

348
00:40:46.193 --> 00:40:47.956
I'm sorry.

349
00:40:48.262 --> 00:40:49.661
Barda. you can't just...

350
00:40:49.830 --> 00:40:51.593
Listen to me. it's too late.

351
00:40:51.766 --> 00:40:53.393
Darkseid will control her mind.

352
00:40:53.834 --> 00:40:57.634
Mould her into a killing machine.
Exploit her weaknesses.

353
00:40:59.006 --> 00:41:00.803
Just like he did me.

354
00:41:01.442 --> 00:41:02.466
Barda.

355
00:41:02.643 --> 00:41:05.237
We know you were made
to do terrible things.

356
00:41:05.746 --> 00:41:07.338
No one blames you.

357
00:41:07.515 --> 00:41:09.745
Now he's got Kara. my cousin.

358
00:41:10.584 --> 00:41:13.576
We're going to Apocalypse.
We need your help to get there.

359
00:41:14.955 --> 00:41:18.254
You have no idea what you're up against.

360
00:41:24.498 --> 00:41:26.398
All we ask
is to borrow your Mother Box...

361
00:41:26.567 --> 00:41:28.797
...so we can generate a boom tube
to get there.

362
00:41:29.170 --> 00:41:31.229
It sounds as if you think
you're coming back.

363
00:41:31.405 --> 00:41:32.463
We'll get back.

364
00:41:32.973 --> 00:41:35.339
There are no exits
from that inferno. Superman.

365
00:41:35.509 --> 00:41:37.568
The entire planet is a death-trap.

366
00:41:38.579 --> 00:41:40.137
It was a mistake to come.

367
00:41:40.314 --> 00:41:42.441
If Barda refuses to help. how are we...?

368
00:41:42.616 --> 00:41:44.413
I'll help you get to Apocalypse.

369
00:41:44.585 --> 00:41:46.712
On one condition.

370
00:41:48.355 --> 00:41:49.652
I'm going with you.

371
00:41:49.824 --> 00:41:51.155
- Barda.
- No way.

372
00:41:51.325 --> 00:41:54.419
I know Darkseid's fortress
like the back of my hand.

373
00:41:54.595 --> 00:41:56.995
You need me. so get over it.

374
00:42:05.473 --> 00:42:08.340
I'm over it. What about you two?

375
00:42:51.886 --> 00:42:53.478
No place like home.

376
00:42:53.654 --> 00:42:56.054
Smells like death.

377
00:42:56.223 --> 00:42:58.020
You think Darkseid knows we're here?

378
00:42:58.626 --> 00:43:00.355
He knows.

379
00:45:06.420 --> 00:45:08.513
Well. I guess that warmed us up.

380
00:45:08.923 --> 00:45:12.120
We've gone over the layout of
Darkseid's fortress. We all know our jobs.

381
00:45:15.963 --> 00:45:17.055
Stay sharp.

382
00:45:24.371 --> 00:45:25.929
Good luck.

383
00:45:29.510 --> 00:45:31.068
I guess we'll take the low road.

384
00:45:31.245 --> 00:45:33.270
After you.

385
00:46:08.682 --> 00:46:12.846
This might not be the right time. but
you've always been an inspiration to me.

386
00:46:13.354 --> 00:46:15.515
- Barda.
- Seriously. Diana.

387
00:46:15.689 --> 00:46:19.682
When someone brings hope
to another person. it's a gift.

388
00:46:28.135 --> 00:46:30.194
And growing up in this hell-hole...

389
00:46:30.371 --> 00:46:34.501
Where you grew up. Barda.
is where you will die.

390
00:46:39.279 --> 00:46:42.271
Well. well. the gang's all here.

391
00:46:46.920 --> 00:46:48.751
You should never have come back. Barda.

392
00:46:48.922 --> 00:46:52.449
Although. personally.
I look forward to watching you die.

393
00:46:52.626 --> 00:46:54.719
I'd tell you to go to hell. Gillotina...

394
00:46:54.895 --> 00:46:57.728
...but given the situation.
that'd be redundant.

395
00:47:00.034 --> 00:47:02.195
They'll go for position.
try to separate us.

396
00:47:02.369 --> 00:47:03.393
Let them try.

397
00:47:04.071 --> 00:47:07.529
Furies. destroy them.

398
00:47:26.560 --> 00:47:29.927
- Damn.
- Bring the intruder's head to Darkseid.

399
00:47:45.612 --> 00:47:48.775
Glory to the one
who takes the life of the Kryptonian.

400
00:47:51.652 --> 00:47:53.313
Hail Darkseid.

401
00:49:01.155 --> 00:49:04.352
- They're very good.
- They should be. I trained them.

402
00:49:19.973 --> 00:49:21.133
Great.

403
00:49:27.147 --> 00:49:29.877
Okay. boys. chew on this.

404
00:50:05.352 --> 00:50:06.614
Bingo.

405
00:50:08.488 --> 00:50:10.649
Hell-spores.

406
00:50:11.458 --> 00:50:15.451
Enough power here to blow a hole
straight to the planet's core.

407
00:50:38.418 --> 00:50:39.851
Darkseid.

408
00:50:40.020 --> 00:50:41.214
Kill them.

409
00:51:28.302 --> 00:51:31.294
- Thanks.
- Don't mention it.

410
00:51:31.571 --> 00:51:33.300
Diana.

411
00:51:38.378 --> 00:51:40.107
Nice try.

412
00:51:44.551 --> 00:51:46.519
Let's see you smile now.

413
00:51:46.687 --> 00:51:49.349
Surrender. Amazon.

414
00:51:52.726 --> 00:51:57.095
- Barda.
- Surrender now. or the bitch dies.

415
00:51:57.264 --> 00:51:59.755
No. Diana. let them kill me.

416
00:51:59.933 --> 00:52:01.457
Never surrender.

417
00:52:03.637 --> 00:52:07.095
Imagine how pleased Darkseid will be.

418
00:52:07.274 --> 00:52:10.801
Why settle for some girl
who fell to Earth...

419
00:52:10.977 --> 00:52:15.311
...when I can deliver to him
the champion of the Amazons.

420
00:52:20.854 --> 00:52:21.878
Darkseid.

421
00:52:22.789 --> 00:52:25.053
Kara leaves with me.

422
00:52:26.026 --> 00:52:30.622
She's free to leave.
if that is what she desires.

423
00:52:36.903 --> 00:52:38.063
Kara?

424
00:52:41.241 --> 00:52:43.072
Hello. Kal.

425
00:52:44.144 --> 00:52:48.137
- Kara.
- I'm fine. Kal. really.

426
00:52:49.916 --> 00:52:52.749
I don't know what he's done to you.
but the nightmare's over.

427
00:52:52.919 --> 00:52:53.977
You're safe now.

428
00:52:54.154 --> 00:52:57.089
You're right. she is safe now.

429
00:52:58.058 --> 00:52:59.150
Let's go home.

430
00:53:01.862 --> 00:53:03.625
That's the problem. cousin.

431
00:53:03.797 --> 00:53:05.594
I'm not sure where home is.

432
00:53:05.766 --> 00:53:07.256
You're just confused.

433
00:53:08.602 --> 00:53:11.537
I'll be back. You and I have unfinished...

434
00:53:11.705 --> 00:53:14.196
You didn't listen to what Darkseid said.

435
00:53:14.374 --> 00:53:17.639
- Kara.
- You never listen to anyone.

436
00:53:22.382 --> 00:53:25.180
He said I was free to go. if I wanted to.

437
00:53:28.955 --> 00:53:31.355
And I don't want to.

438
00:53:37.063 --> 00:53:41.193
Good. Now kill him.

439
00:53:42.636 --> 00:53:44.695
I won't fight you.

440
00:53:45.405 --> 00:53:49.398
Good. Makes my job that much easier.

441
00:53:58.819 --> 00:54:00.150
What's wrong with the beast?

442
00:54:00.320 --> 00:54:03.153
Must be something he ate.

443
00:54:10.564 --> 00:54:11.861
Take off your armour.

444
00:54:13.366 --> 00:54:14.856
Now.

445
00:54:15.402 --> 00:54:17.302
Let me kill her. Granny.

446
00:54:18.672 --> 00:54:21.869
No. it's me you want. Let her go.

447
00:54:22.042 --> 00:54:26.001
I like to have my cake and eat it too.

448
00:54:26.179 --> 00:54:27.612
Make her bleed.

449
00:54:55.509 --> 00:54:57.409
You were saying. Granny?

450
00:54:58.912 --> 00:55:01.972
Go ahead. Kill me.

451
00:55:02.449 --> 00:55:06.317
- That's what you're programmed to do.
- Barda.

452
00:55:06.653 --> 00:55:08.678
What's the matter. Barda?

453
00:55:08.855 --> 00:55:10.982
You know you want to.

454
00:55:34.281 --> 00:55:37.842
All these years of pretending to be human
have made you soft.

455
00:55:38.385 --> 00:55:42.253
Kara. he's controlling you. Fight it.

456
00:55:43.123 --> 00:55:45.648
Do not hesitate. Kill him.

457
00:55:46.092 --> 00:55:48.458
As you wish. Lord Darkseid.

458
00:56:01.041 --> 00:56:05.671
With your death. cousin.
my life begins here on Apocalypse.

459
00:56:05.845 --> 00:56:06.937
Not if I can help it.

460
00:56:15.255 --> 00:56:17.519
Darkseid said
you wouldn't be up to the challenge.

461
00:56:17.924 --> 00:56:21.690
That your feelings. your beliefs.
would cloud your judgement.

462
00:56:22.596 --> 00:56:26.157
He's right. you know.
Earth does need a new hero.

463
00:56:26.533 --> 00:56:27.864
Not his version.

464
00:56:28.034 --> 00:56:31.663
You think killing me will set you free?
He's just using you.

465
00:56:31.838 --> 00:56:33.897
Liar. He cares about me.

466
00:56:34.074 --> 00:56:36.372
No. Kara. I care about you.

467
00:56:36.543 --> 00:56:39.603
But you won't listen.
His control over you is total.

468
00:56:39.779 --> 00:56:44.239
I see that now.
which is why I have to do this.

469
00:56:50.223 --> 00:56:51.417
It's over. Darkseid.

470
00:56:51.858 --> 00:56:54.918
Even you must realize the folly
of being a king without a kingdom.

471
00:56:55.095 --> 00:56:59.088
I doubt the battle between the Kryptonians
will bring about such destruction.

472
00:56:59.599 --> 00:57:01.362
I'm not talking about them.

473
00:57:01.534 --> 00:57:05.868
Your armoury. the hell-spores.
they've been activated.

474
00:57:06.039 --> 00:57:09.202
Impossible. The arming code is encrypted.

475
00:57:09.376 --> 00:57:12.243
I broke the code
and reprogrammed them.

476
00:57:12.412 --> 00:57:13.436
You're bluffing.

477
00:57:13.613 --> 00:57:16.514
Omega lambda <i>7</i>- X-L-9.

478
00:57:16.683 --> 00:57:18.446
That sound like a bluff to you?

479
00:57:21.054 --> 00:57:24.512
One hell-spore can turn an entire planet
into a fire pit.

480
00:57:24.691 --> 00:57:28.559
What will happen to Apocalypse
when 500 go off simultaneously?

481
00:57:29.162 --> 00:57:32.063
You dare? You dare?

482
00:57:36.870 --> 00:57:41.204
I could destroy you with a single blast
of my omega beams.

483
00:57:41.374 --> 00:57:42.534
You could.

484
00:57:42.709 --> 00:57:44.904
But that wouldn't stop the hell-spores.
would it?

485
00:57:58.825 --> 00:58:00.486
You will disarm them.

486
00:58:00.860 --> 00:58:02.020
Here's the deal.

487
00:58:02.195 --> 00:58:05.562
Release the girl and give your word
you'll leave her alone.

488
00:58:09.769 --> 00:58:12.135
Forswear Kara Zor-El.

489
00:58:19.713 --> 00:58:21.010
Say it.

490
00:58:26.019 --> 00:58:27.316
Well played.

491
00:58:29.522 --> 00:58:34.255
Had the Kryptonian or the Amazon
taken that gamble. they would have lost.

492
00:58:34.427 --> 00:58:36.554
They do not have the strength
of character...

493
00:58:36.730 --> 00:58:40.097
...to destroy an entire planet
to achieve success.

494
00:58:40.900 --> 00:58:42.891
But you. a human?

495
00:58:43.069 --> 00:58:45.765
You kill your own kind to win battles.

496
00:58:45.939 --> 00:58:47.770
An admirable quality.

497
00:58:47.941 --> 00:58:49.169
Take the girl.

498
00:58:49.342 --> 00:58:51.401
I will make no move against her.

499
00:59:00.787 --> 00:59:02.152
I'll hold you to that.

500
00:59:05.558 --> 00:59:07.389
We'll all hold you to it.

501
00:59:17.303 --> 00:59:20.033
Mercy. Barda? Disappointing.

502
00:59:28.648 --> 00:59:30.013
Disarm the hell-spores.

503
00:59:30.683 --> 00:59:32.514
Leave Apocalypse.

504
00:59:51.971 --> 00:59:53.233
Hey.

505
00:59:53.406 --> 00:59:54.668
Am I dreaming?

506
00:59:55.074 --> 00:59:56.166
What happened?

507
00:59:56.342 --> 00:59:58.810
I don't remember anything after...

508
01:00:00.313 --> 01:00:01.871
Lyla.

509
01:00:08.021 --> 01:00:10.012
You're safe now.

510
01:00:14.394 --> 01:00:16.362
It's nothing. Just a scratch.

511
01:00:17.597 --> 01:00:21.033
I remember dreaming.
a horrible nightmare.

512
01:00:21.201 --> 01:00:23.499
All I wanted to do was get home.

513
01:00:23.670 --> 01:00:26.195
I did terrible things.

514
01:00:26.639 --> 01:00:28.732
Darkseid lives for manipulation.

515
01:00:28.908 --> 01:00:32.537
He has hypnotists.
scientists and sadists...

516
01:00:32.712 --> 01:00:35.545
...whose only functions
are to break your spirit.

517
01:00:35.715 --> 01:00:37.706
Darkseid is evil.

518
01:00:38.117 --> 01:00:41.382
But did he influence me?

519
01:00:41.554 --> 01:00:44.045
Or just bring out a darkness
that is already there?

520
01:00:44.490 --> 01:00:46.253
You're here with me.

521
01:00:46.426 --> 01:00:48.724
And you're okay. Nothing else matters.

522
01:00:52.899 --> 01:00:56.699
You said to me once
you didn't wanna be anybody's champion.

523
01:00:56.870 --> 01:00:59.498
When you're strong.
there's somewhere I want to take you.

524
01:00:59.672 --> 01:01:02.140
Where you can be safe.
Where you can fit in.

525
01:01:02.308 --> 01:01:05.072
Where you can just be yourself.

526
01:01:18.491 --> 01:01:20.152
You're sure it's a good idea?

527
01:01:20.326 --> 01:01:22.055
It feels right.

528
01:01:23.763 --> 01:01:27.358
- Can't let it rest. can you?
- Knock it off. you two.

529
01:01:34.474 --> 01:01:35.498
Lyla.

530
01:01:35.675 --> 01:01:38.337
I'm going to miss you more
than you can even imagine.

531
01:01:38.511 --> 01:01:42.106
You were my first friend
and you accepted me without question.

532
01:01:42.282 --> 01:01:45.979
Maybe because as Harbinger
you saw something in me that's worthwhile.

533
01:01:46.753 --> 01:01:49.654
Now. all I have to do is find that thing.

534
01:01:53.359 --> 01:01:55.759
I'll try not to disappoint you.

535
01:02:02.201 --> 01:02:04.669
Diana. I can't thank you enough.

536
01:02:08.341 --> 01:02:10.172
You will always have a home here.

537
01:02:13.246 --> 01:02:14.907
Alura.

538
01:02:16.950 --> 01:02:20.113
You once asked
if I could remember my mother's name.

539
01:02:20.286 --> 01:02:22.117
It was Alura.

540
01:02:25.291 --> 01:02:28.192
Kal. I'm ready now.

541
01:02:32.699 --> 01:02:35.862
- Thank you.
- You still owe me a computer.

542
01:02:36.035 --> 01:02:39.436
Might take a while. Reporter's salary.

543
01:02:42.942 --> 01:02:45.342
Always has to have the last word.

544
01:03:00.893 --> 01:03:03.191
Welcome to Smallville.

545
01:03:26.853 --> 01:03:28.878
This is where you grew up?

546
01:03:30.256 --> 01:03:31.280
It's not so bad.

547
01:03:31.457 --> 01:03:32.924
No. I didn't mean...

548
01:03:33.092 --> 01:03:36.960
It's just so different
compared to Krypton.

549
01:03:37.130 --> 01:03:38.154
Even Metropolis.

550
01:03:49.142 --> 01:03:51.337
I think I'm going to like it here.

551
01:03:51.944 --> 01:03:53.275
It can be a little quiet.

552
01:03:53.446 --> 01:03:56.609
Kal. I've been chased.
shot at. kidnapped...

553
01:03:56.783 --> 01:04:01.277
...beaten up.
had my mind controlled and I broke a nail.

554
01:04:01.454 --> 01:04:03.012
I'm ready for a little quiet.

555
01:04:05.391 --> 01:04:09.384
If I know my mother. she'll have some
of her famous apple pie waiting.

556
01:04:10.596 --> 01:04:12.154
You okay?

557
01:04:12.832 --> 01:04:14.766
Little nervous. I guess.

558
01:04:14.934 --> 01:04:16.868
It's just. you have this life.

559
01:04:17.437 --> 01:04:19.928
You can be Clark. or Kal-El.
or Superman.

560
01:04:21.107 --> 01:04:22.870
Even a son.

561
01:04:23.309 --> 01:04:24.606
Who am I going to be?

562
01:04:25.144 --> 01:04:27.840
I can't answer that. Kara. only you can.

563
01:04:28.281 --> 01:04:30.249
Whatever you decide.
I'll be there for you.

564
01:04:30.416 --> 01:04:31.815
I promise.

565
01:04:31.984 --> 01:04:34.612
Now. come on.
Let's go meet the folks.

566
01:04:45.965 --> 01:04:49.059
I gave my word
I would not come for the girl.

567
01:04:51.404 --> 01:04:56.364
Your death. however.
is long overdue. Superman.

568
01:04:59.512 --> 01:05:01.002
Kal. Uh!

569
01:05:03.116 --> 01:05:04.913
Kara. no!

570
01:05:13.759 --> 01:05:15.488
Stupid girl.

571
01:05:16.529 --> 01:05:18.929
You murdering...

572
01:05:20.666 --> 01:05:22.691
Time to die. Man of Steel.

573
01:05:39.318 --> 01:05:40.342
Darkseid.

574
01:05:52.798 --> 01:05:54.390
There's more where that came from.

575
01:05:54.934 --> 01:05:57.232
Fearless. Untapped power.

576
01:05:57.837 --> 01:06:01.705
It would have been a glorious life for you.
captain of my honour guard.

577
01:06:01.874 --> 01:06:06.243
Instead. my omega beams
will reduce you to ashes.

578
01:06:06.412 --> 01:06:08.243
Take your best shot.

579
01:08:26.319 --> 01:08:27.650
Impressive.

580
01:08:27.820 --> 01:08:32.416
Under my guidance. you could have become
the most powerful being in the universe.

581
01:08:32.925 --> 01:08:36.759
Your life here
will be nothing in comparison.

582
01:08:37.663 --> 01:08:39.597
But it'll be my life.

583
01:09:08.928 --> 01:09:11.988
We will meet again. Kryptonian.

584
01:09:22.074 --> 01:09:25.407
You didn't think
you could just walk away. did you?

585
01:11:05.644 --> 01:11:11.640
Don't ever come here again.
or you won't be going back.

586
01:11:39.745 --> 01:11:42.942
That should give him something
to think about back on Apocalypse.

587
01:11:43.115 --> 01:11:45.549
Apocalypse? I'm not so sure.

588
01:11:46.151 --> 01:11:47.175
While you were busy...

589
01:11:47.353 --> 01:11:50.754
...I took the liberty of reconfiguring
the boom tube's coordinates.

590
01:11:50.923 --> 01:11:52.481
Something Darkseid taught me...

591
01:11:52.658 --> 01:11:55.559
...that I'm guessing
he's probably regretting about now.

592
01:12:02.101 --> 01:12:04.865
I don't think he'll be a problem again.

593
01:12:06.272 --> 01:12:09.139
Not until someone
thaws him out anyway.

594
01:12:14.980 --> 01:12:19.610
Kal. there was a moment there
when I thought you were dead.

595
01:12:19.785 --> 01:12:21.685
And I realized. ever since I arrived...

596
01:12:21.854 --> 01:12:25.813
...I've been running away from who I am
and what I'm meant to be.

597
01:12:27.359 --> 01:12:29.259
I've made a decision. Kal.

598
01:12:29.428 --> 01:12:31.089
I know what I want to do.

599
01:12:35.167 --> 01:12:36.532
Uh-oh.

600
01:12:53.419 --> 01:12:56.718
Mom. Dad. this is Kara.

601
01:12:56.889 --> 01:12:58.948
My cousin? Your niece?

602
01:12:59.124 --> 01:13:01.854
Mr. Kent. Mrs. Kent.

603
01:13:02.027 --> 01:13:03.892
It's so nice to finally meet you.

604
01:13:04.063 --> 01:13:06.361
I've heard so much about you both.

605
01:13:10.703 --> 01:13:12.534
Don't worry.
I can build you a new one.

606
01:13:12.705 --> 01:13:14.605
I can help. I'm great with a hammer.

607
01:13:14.773 --> 01:13:16.798
I can pound.

608
01:13:16.976 --> 01:13:18.068
I'm a good pounder.

609
01:13:28.654 --> 01:13:30.417
I know how busy you all are...

610
01:13:30.589 --> 01:13:33.820
...but it's only appropriate
that you should be the first to hear.

611
01:13:33.993 --> 01:13:38.191
You. who would put your lives
on the line for a perfect stranger.

612
01:13:38.797 --> 01:13:42.426
We're all alike. for each of us.
in our own way...

613
01:13:42.601 --> 01:13:44.694
...had to struggle to become who we are.

614
01:13:45.070 --> 01:13:49.029
But what better role
for anyone to aspire to. than hero?

615
01:13:49.575 --> 01:13:53.875
So allow me to reintroduce my cousin.
Kara Zor-El.

616
01:13:54.046 --> 01:13:58.676
Or as the world
will come to know her. Supergirl.

617
01:14:03.789 --> 01:14:07.725
To be honest. I'm not sure
I've earned the right to wear this uniform.

618
01:14:08.327 --> 01:14:09.885
But I will.

619
01:14:50.769 --> 01:14:51.793
Hey.

620
01:14:52.305 --> 01:15:52.932
